-- AC Milan Vies With Chelsea, Man. United for Guardiola: Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-11-14T11:21:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-14/ac-milan-vies-with-chelsea-man-united-for-guardiola-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers with clickable Internet links.  Guardiola Watch  AC Milan intensified efforts to hire former Barcelona coach
Josep Guardiola, who is also a target for Chelsea and  Manchester
United , the  Daily Mail  reported.  Guardiola, 41, is midway through a year-long sabbatical
from soccer, the Mail said.  Anelka Return  Queens Park Rangers want  Nicolas Anelka  to help them move
out of the relegation zone,  the Sun  reported.  Anelka, who is unsettled at Shanghai Shenhua, would rather
return to former club Liverpool, the Sun said.  Wenger Strategy  Arsenal coach Arsene Wenger may employ a five-man defense
after the Gunners conceded 15 goals in seven games, the  Daily
Mail  reported.  Wenger held a training-ground meeting to discuss changing
the team’s 4-3-2-1 formation, the Mail said.  England Flops  Steven Gerrard  said he would give his England career so far
a “six or seven” out of 10 as he prepares for his 100th game,
 the Guardian  reported.  There have been no “real heroes” for the team since
England won the  World Cup  in 1966, Gerrard is quoted as saying.  To contact the reporters on this story:
